               <p>ROBERT PEARCE. I am a <rs id="t18260511-137-viclabel784" type="occupation">plumber</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260511-137-victim759 t18260511-137-viclabel784"></join> and <rs id="t18260511-137-viclabel785" type="occupation">glazier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260511-137-victim759 t18260511-137-viclabel785"></join>, and live in King-street, Long-acre. On the 7th of May, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I was in front of the Horse Guards; I had a handkerchief in my right-hand coat pocket. The officer came, and said I was robbed - I put my hand to my pocket, and missed my handkerchief - I had it a few minutes before; he had hold of the prisoner close to me. I saw him take my handkerchief from him.</p>
               <p>
            
